1. Select your bucket
2. > Properties > scroll down > Static website hosting
3. Static website hosting > Enable
4. Index document > index.html
5. Save changes

6. In permissions > Block public access (bucket settings)
7. Uncheck and Confirm

8. Edit the Bucket policy with this code




{
    "Version": "2012-10-17",
    "Statement": [
        {
            "Sid": "PublicReadGetObject",
            "Effect": "Allow",
            "Principal": "*",
            "Action": "s3:GetObject",
            "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::NAME_OF_BUCKET/*"
        }
    ]
}

9. Replace NAME_OF_BUCKET by the name of your bucket.
10. Save changes

11. Upload index.html if not done
12. The public URL is > Properties > Static website hosting > URL is available
